gametext: USED: Place out of play any one of the following from your hand: Attack Run, You're All Clear Kid, Death Star: Trench or Rebel Tech. Retrieve 1 Force. LOST: Use 3 Force to retrieve Attack Run.
lore: Early warning and careful planning allow the Rebels to achieve maximum readiness while still maintaining optimal flexibility.
name: Advance Preparation

gametext: Use 3 Force to cancel a battle just initiated at a system or sector. OR Cancel Besieged. OR Release (move for free) all your characters from a captured starship to your side of any docking bay site.
lore: The Rebellion's limited resources force it to consider the wisdom of any military encounter. In many cases, retreat or deception is a preferable recourse.
name: Alternatives To Fighting

gametext: Power +1 under "nighttime conditions." May move away from a battle at same site as a 'react.'
lore: Unut Poll is a typical male Arcona. Unlike many other Arcona, he has avoided salt. \b Scout\b0  known to cooperate with Alliance operatives.
name: Arcona

gametext: Deploy on Death Star: Trench. \par During your move phase, you may make an Attack Run as follows: \par \b Enter Trench:\b0  Move up to 3 of your starfighters into trench (for free). Dark Side may immediately follow with up to 3 TIEs (for free). \par \b Provide Cover:\b0  Identify your lead starfighter (Proton Torpedoes* required) and wingmen (if any). Turbolaser Batteries and TIEs with weapons may now target your starfighters (wingmen first, then lead if no wingmen remaining). Hit starfighters are immediately lost.  \par \b It's Away!:\b0  Draw two destiny. \par \b Pull Up!:\b0  All starfighters now move to Death Star system (for free). If (total destiny +X +Y -Z) > 15, Death Star is "blown away."  \par X = ability of lead pilot or 3 if Targeting Computer is present. \par Y = total sites at largest Rebel Base (Yavin 4 or Hoth). \par Z = highest ability of TIE pilots in trench. \par *Your proton torpedoes are immune to Overload.
name: Attack Run

gametext: If a battle was just initiated at an interior site, use 1 Force; for remainder of battle, all characters of ability > 2 and all leaders (on both sides) are simultaneously excluded from that battle.
lore: When Vader turned his attention to the escaping Rebels, Han immediately offered Luke some sage advice.
name: Blast The Door, Kid!

gametext: USED: Select a player to activate 1 Force. LOST: Cancel Juri Juice or Hypo.
lore: Nutrient-rich beverage common in moisture farm communities. Rumored to have medicinal qualities. Popular in cantinas among those who can't hold their juri juice.
name: Blue Milk

gametext: Use X Force to deploy on your warrior, where X = (7 - warrior's power). X cannot fall below 1. May target a character or creature using X Force. Draw destiny. Add 1 if targeting a character, 2 if targeting a creature. Target hit if total destiny > defense value.
lore: Hand-crafted weapon of choice among Wookiees. Fires explosive 'quarrels' (which look like blaster bolts). Requires great strength to use. Extra ammo carried on bandoliers.
name: Bowcaster

gametext: * Power = Sqrt(3(X-Y) +2 (A-B)+pi) (minimum power=1). X = Dark Side hand cards; Y = Light Side hand cards; A = total number of (Dark Side Force icon) icons in play; B = total number of (Light Side Force icon) icons in play; pi=3.141592653589793238462643383...
lore: BoShek nicknamed this male Siniteen 'Brainiac' due to his ability to calculate hyperspace coordinates in his head. "He's the brains, sweetheart!"
name: Brainiac

gametext: Deploy on any Death Star site except Docking Bay 327. Target your spy or leader not on Death Star. When target reaches Utinni Effect, draw destiny. Release that many captives from the Detention Block Corridor. Lose Utinni Effect.
lore: "Aren't you a little short for a stormtrooper?"
name: Cell 2187

gametext: Power +1 at same location as Han. Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. When piloting \ul Falcon\ul0, also adds 1 to maneuver. Your vehicles, starships, and droids at same site that are 'hit' and about to be lost go to Used Pile instead.
lore: Wookiee \b smuggler\b0  from Kashyyyk. Over 200 years old. Top-notch mechanic and pilot. Jabba has large bounty on this "walking carpet." Friends call him Chewie ... or Fuzzball.
name: Chewbacca

dark_side_text: If you control, each Bith character is destiny -1 and Ghhhk is power +2 in battles at a holosite.
gametext: If you occupy, each Bith character is destiny +2.   If you control, each Bith character is destiny -1 and Ghhhk is power +2 in battles at a holosite.
light_side_text: If you occupy, each Bith character is destiny +2.
name: Clak'dor VII

gametext: When at a Yavin 4, Hoth or Endor site, Rebel starships may move to the related system as a 'react.'
lore: Popular \b leader\b0  whose expertise in space defense and orbital battle stations enabled the Alliance to uncover a fatal flaw in the Death Star's design.
name: Commander Evram Lajaie

gametext: When at a war room you control, adds 1 to power of each Rebel starship at the related system. May use 1 Force to cancel Astromech Shortage.
lore: \b Leader\b0  of Rebel forces on Yavin 4. Formerly Suolriep sector HQ commander. As a Rebel \b spy\b0, aided Princess Leia and Bail Organa in the years prior to the Senate's dissolution.
name: Commander Vanden Willard

gametext: Deploy on a superlaser. May not fire at a planet until 'recharged.' Opponent may use Force (stacking it here); accumulating 8 Force recharges superlaser. When fired at a planet, Effect is canceled. If Effect canceled, accumulated Force is placed in Used Pile.
lore: The huge strain on the little-tested power generator matrix of the superlaser's fusion reactor can require full recharging before the system can be used again.
name: Commence Recharging

dark_side_text: Each of your starships are hyperspeed +1 when moving from here.
gametext: Your \ul Falcon\ul0  and your Corellian corvettes may deploy here as a 'react.'   Each of your starships are hyperspeed +1 when moving from here.
light_side_text: Your \ul Falcon\ul0  and your Corellian corvettes may deploy here as a 'react.'
name: Corellia

gametext: Once per turn, one weapon or device is deploy -1 onto a Rebel at same site.
lore: Brindy Truchong is a typical female Corellian \b smuggler\b0. Her goal in Mos Eisley is to find a quick means of providing supplies to the Rebellion.
name: Corellian

gametext: If opponent just initiated a Tallon Roll, add your maneuver + ability of one pilot on your targeted starfighter to your total. OR Decrease the maneuver of an opponent's starfighter by 1 for remainder of this turn.
lore: First perfected by Corellian starship battle tacticians, this dangerous counter-maneuver has saved numerous hot-shot pilots in life-or-death situations.
name: Corellian Slip

dark_side_text: "Trench Rules" in effect, your weapons fire free and Turbolaser Battery may deploy here.
gametext: "Trench Rules" in effect and each of your starfighters is maneuver -2 here.   "Trench Rules" in effect, your weapons fire free and Turbolaser Battery may deploy here.
light_side_text: "Trench Rules" in effect and each of your starfighters is maneuver -2 here.
name: Death Star: Trench

dark_side_text: "Dejarik Rules" in effect here. Site converted by Imperial Holotable.
gametext: "Dejarik Rules" in effect here.   "Dejarik Rules" in effect here. Site converted by Imperial Holotable.
name: Dejarik Hologameboard

gametext: For each other musician at same site, the ability required to draw battle destiny here increases by 1 for both players.
lore: Male Bith \b musician\b0. Plays Fizzz (Dorenian Beshniquel) in Figrin D'an's band. Frustrated by sentients, especially humans, he prefers to work with droids.
name: Doikk Na'ts

gametext: If both players have a spy at same site, draw destiny. Add 2 if opponent's spy is Undercover. Opponent's spy is lost if destiny > 2. OR Opponent's Tonnika Sisters present at a site cross to your side.
lore: Typical of impersonators, Shada double-crossed everyone. Her true affiliations still remain a mystery.
name: Double Agent

gametext: Use 1 Force to target a starfighter having one or more permanent pilots. Draw destiny. If destiny > 2, deploy on starfighter to remove all permanent pilots (otherwise, Effect is lost). May add one pilot for each permanent pilot removed. (Immune to Alter.)
lore: The Guidenhouser ejection seat has saved many pilots from their exploding starships. However, system malfunctions have sometimes caused spontaneous ejection.
name: Eject! Eject!

gametext: Deploy on your astromech droid. Cancels an 'exploding' Program Trap here. Any starship it is aboard is immune to Lateral Damage and ion cannons. If deployed on R2-D2, may lose Fire Extinguisher to cancel a battle just initiated where present at a site.
lore: Among the various special devices on droids like R2 units are gas-based fire extinguishers. Effective against electrical fires and can cause confusion during battle.
name: Fire Extinguisher

gametext: Adds 1 to power of anything he pilots. Adds 1 to forfeit of each of your characters at same Tatooine site. Subtracts 1 from forfeit of each of opponent's characters at same Hoth site. Game text suspended if at same site as a tax collector.
lore: Free-trader who imports ice chunks from rings of Ohann and Adriana, outer planets in Tatoo system. Sales remain cold ... due to steep Imperial taxes and bribes.
name: Garouf Lafoe

gametext: May add 2 pilots or passengers. May forfeit in place of your other starfighter 'hit' in Death Star: Trench, restoring that starfighter to normal.
lore: Tiree's Y-wing during the Battle of Yavin. Custom high-power lateral thrusters provide enhanced maneuverability, allowing Gold 2 to better draw and evade enemy fire.
name: Gold 2

gametext: If opponent just played an Interrupt, use 1 Force to deploy on table. That Interrupt is played out but is then 'grappled' (placed here but is out of play). Any new Interrupts of the same name are now unique (*). (Immune to Control.)
lore: Stormtrooper utility belts contain basic tools such as a grappling hook to grab onto protrusions. The hook can also be used to ensnare escaping targets.
name: Grappling Hook

gametext: USED: If opponent has 13 or more cards in hand, place all but 8 (random selection) in Used Pile. LOST: Cancel Molator (even at a holosite). OR Use 4 Force to reveal opponent's hand. All cards opponent has two or more of in hand are lost.
lore: \b Dejarik\b0  representation of mythical Molator guardian. The spirit of Grimtaash is said to protect Alderaanian royalty from corruption and betrayal.
name: Grimtaash

gametext: * Deploys only on Tatooine for 2 Force from each player's Force Pile. Het is power +1 for each stormtrooper at same site, unless Reegesk is present.
lore: Jawa \b scout\b0. Wants to avenge deaths of relatives killed in stormtrooper assault on sandcrawler. Reegesk pilfered the powerpack from his blaster at a critical moment.
name: Het Nkik

gametext: During the damage segment of a battle you lost, if you have no cards left that can be forfeited, cancel all remaining battle damage. (Immune to Sense.) OR Cancel Sunsdown.
lore: \b Dejarik\b0  creature. These ferocious-looking beasts are gentle, loyal, and often domesticated as guard animals or pets on Kinyen, the Gran homeworld.
name: Houjix

gametext: On a hunch, if opponent just initiated a Force drain at an adjacent site, you may use 1 Force to search opponent's Force Pile and place out of play one card there that has 'back' in the title; reshuffle.
lore: What hump?
name: Hunchback

gametext: If opponent just deployed four or more characters to same location this turn, prevent all of those characters from battling this turn. OR If opponent just 'reacted' to a battle, cancel the battle.
lore: "Look at him, he's heading for that small moon." Luke became apprehensive when Obi-Wan informed him, "That's no moon. It's a space station."
name: I Have A Very Bad Feeling About This

gametext: If you have a spy present at the Detention Block Corridor, target a captive there. Draw destiny. If destiny + ability of spy > ability of captive, target is released. Otherwise, spy is captured. OR Cancel Spice Mines Of Kessel (releasing targeted captive).
lore: "Huh?"
name: I'm Here To Rescue You

gametext: Opponent must use X Force when Force draining at any adjacent site, where X = the number of other musicians present with Ickabel.
lore: Male Bith \b musician\b0. His favorite cantina song is "Tears of Aquanna" (mainly because it features him on Fanfar).
name: Ickabel G'ont

gametext: May add 1 passenger. Permanent pilot provides ability of 1. May move as a 'react.' * Landspeed = 4. OR 1 character may shuttle to or from same site for free.
lore: \b Enclosed\b0  vehicle used for shuttling and hot-rodding. E-16/x ion engine pushes T-16 up to 1200 kph.
name: Incom T-16 Skyhopper

gametext: Use 1 Force to deploy on your Jawa, 3 on your warrior. May target a character using 1 Force. Draw destiny. Targeted droid stolen if destiny +1 > forfeit. Targeted non-droid character excluded from battle if destiny = defense value.
lore: Cobbled-together weapon built from salvaged power cells, droid restraining bolts and an ion accelerator. Fires a stream of ion energy that stuns droids and irritates others.
name: Jawa Ion Gun

dark_side_text: Total ability of 6 or more required for you to draw battle destiny here.
gametext: Your Wookiees and smugglers deploy -2 here.   Total ability of 6 or more required for you to draw battle destiny here.
light_side_text: Your Wookiees and smugglers deploy -2 here.
name: Kashyyyk

gametext: During a battle at a holosite, add one battle destiny. OR Target an opponent's character of ability < 5 present with your Wookiee that just participated in a battle you lost; character is Disarmed (power -1 and may no longer carry weapons). Stack on that character.
lore: "It's not wise to upset a Wookiee." "But sir, nobody worries about upsetting a droid." "That's 'cause a droid don't pull people's arms out of their sockets when they lose."
name: Let The Wookiee Win

gametext: Use 3 Force to deploy on opponent's side of table. All opponent's TIEs are deploy +1.
lore: The Empire's tremendous military machine requires extensive coordination at every level. Slight errors in any step can quickly escalate supply delays.
name: Logistical Delay

gametext: Use 2 Force to deploy on a Rebel or alien. If Luke's Cape is not at a Tatooine location, your total Force generation is +1. That character is immune to attrition < 3.
lore: A symbol of the adventurous pilot and the awakening of his destiny. "You've taken your first step into a larger world."
name: Luke's Cape

gametext: Use 1 Force to deploy on Luke or Owen Lars, 3 on your non-droid character. May target a character or creature using 1 Force. Draw destiny. Subtract 1 if targeting a character. Add 2 if targeting a creature. Target hit if total destiny > defense value.
lore: Czerka 6-2Aug2. Extended barrel provides long-range targeting without expensive laser sight. Sturdy construction, but no match for a Tusken Raider's gaderffi stick.
name: Luke's Hunting Rifle

gametext: Adds 2 to forfeit of each non-droid character at same and adjacent sites. At any time, any player may use 1 Force to turn M-HYD off (face down) or on again (face up).
lore: Pretentious hydroponics droid. Specializes in working with binary load lifters and vaporators. Proficient in a number of languages but prefers to converse only in binary.
name: M-HYD 'Binary' Droid

gametext: Deploy on your sandcrawler. Once during each of your control phases, may target one character present. Draw destiny. If destiny > character's ability, "suck up" character (relocate to related interior sandcrawler site or owner's Used Pile).
lore: Retractable tube originally designed to collect mined materials for transport to refining facilities. Jawas now use it to suck up droids (and anything else that's not nailed down).
name: Magnetic Suction Tube

gametext: Deploy on your non-thief to give that character \b thief\b0  skill. Once during each of your control phases, may target one device at same site. Draw destiny. If destiny < target's destiny number, it is stolen. OR Deploy on a weapon to prevent theft. (Immune to Alter.)
lore: A crafty purloiner from Tirac Munda with a heart of gold. Often hired to advise the wealthy on how to protect their own property. Well traveled and skilled in many languages.
name: Merc Sunlet

gametext: Deploys for 1 Force to an unoccupied site. Deploys and moves like an undercover spy. When present with Motti (or pilot) of ability < 3, choose one to be immediately lost (treat as an "all cards" situation). Seeker is also lost.
lore: Military version of a 'remote.' Programmed to stalk specific targets or secondary targets. Heat and light sensors track with fatal accuracy. Can stow away on starships.
name: Motti Seeker

gametext: After using Bith Shuffle, peek at top X cards of pile or deck just shuffled, where X = number of other musicians at same site. May reshuffle without peeking.
lore: Male Bith \b musician\b0. Though he enjoys playing his Bandfill in Figrin D'an's band, he misses the bubbling pink swamps of his homeworld, Clak'dor VII.
name: Nalan Cheel

gametext: During your control phase, use 2 Force to release a starship held by any Tractor Beam. (Not effective on Death Star Tractor Beam if Central Core in play.) OR Randomly select one card from opponent's Lost Pile or Blaster Rack and place out of play.
lore: "I hope that old man got that tractor beam out of commission or this is gonna be a real short trip."
name: Out Of Commission

gametext: If Elis Helrot just completed a transport, use 2 Force. Elis and all characters transported are lost. (Immune to Sense.) OR Prevent a just-deployed smuggler from moving this turn.
lore: Smugglers and other rogues frequent spaceports along trade routes. "Your friend is quite a mercenary. I wonder if he really cares about anything, or anybody."
name: Quite A Mercenary

gametext: While aboard any starfighter, adds 2 to power, maneuver and hyperspeed (3 on Red 5). If at a Scomp link when opponent draws destiny of: 1-3, you may activate one Force; 4-6, you may draw top card from Reserve Deck.
lore: Fiesty. Loyal. Heroic. Insecure. Rebel \b spy\b0. Excels at trouble. Incorrigible counterpart of a mindless philosopher. Has picked up a slight flutter. A bit eccentric.
name: R2-D2 (Artoo-Detoo)

gametext: While aboard any starship, adds 1 to power and maneuver. During your control phase, if aboard your starship damaged by an ion cannon, restores armor/maneuver and hyperspeed.
lore: Cheap astromech droid commonly referred to as 'Red.' Purposely blew his motivator to prevent splitting up R2-D2 and C-3PO on Tatooine. Poor navigator but skilled mechanic.
name: R5-D4 (Arfive-Defour)

gametext: May transfer character weapons (for free) to or from your other characters present. May carry up to four such weapons at one time.
lore: The RA line of servant droids has fifth-degree primary programming. Low intelligence with capabilities for menial labor only. Common among nobles and high-ranking officials.
name: RA-7 (Aray-Seven)

gametext: Your starships may move here as a 'react.'   Your capital starships deploy -2 here.
light_side_text: Your starships may move here as a 'react.'
name: Ralltiir

gametext: Adds 1 to forfeit of each of your other Rebels (except leaders) at same site. Bothan spies deploy free to same location.
lore: Commander Bob Hudsol. Typical of hard-line Corellian officers known for caution in battle. \b Leader\b0  of resistance in Bothan space. Developed strong ties to Bothan spynet.
name: Rebel Commander

gametext: Adds 1 to forfeit of your other troopers and Rebel Guards at same site. When moving with a 'squad' of exactly three other troopers and/or Rebel Guards, all four move for 1 Force. Rebel Guards at same site may move.
lore: Lt. Pello Scrambas is a typical veteran officer in the Rebel forces. Loyally served the Organa family for nearly two decades as a guard for the Royal House of Alderaan.
name: Rebel Squad Leader

gametext: When at your war room: \b Cumulatively\b0  adds 1 to total of Attack Run. OR Once during each of your control phases, may send this tech to your Used Pile and take Death Star: Trench into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle.
lore: Def Goren, typical expert in communications and scanner jamming, served aboard the Rebel privateer corvette \ul Spiral\ul0  before joining the Alliance High Command.
name: Rebel Tech

gametext: Use 1 Force to deploy on your starship. You may deploy cards as a 'react' to a battle at same system or sector.
lore: Fabritech communications and sensor array. Features active/passive scanners, powerful jamming system, ship-to-ship transmitters and short-range target acquisition program.
name: Rectenna

gametext: May add 1 pilot and 1 astromech. Immune to attrition < 3 if Wedge piloting.
lore: Wedge's X-wing at Battle of Yavin. Wedge had to nurse the fighter home after a hit in the Death Star trench destroyed its micro-maneuvering controls.
name: Red 2

gametext: May add 1 pilot and 1 astromech. Immune to attrition < 4 if Luke piloting. When firing in an Attack Run, adds 1 to total.
lore: Luke's Incom T-65 X-wing at the Battle of Yavin. Instrumentation similarities between Red 5 and the T-16 skyhopper allowed Luke to play a pivotal role in the conflict.
name: Red 5

gametext: May add 1 pilot. Opponent may add 2 to destiny drawn for I've Got A Problem Here when targeting Red 6.
lore: Jek Porkins' X-wing at Battle of Yavin. Instrumental in success of strafing attacks against Death Star. Skipped last inspection of computer and flight control systems.
name: Red 6

gametext: Use 1 Force to deploy at any site. Moves like a character at normal use of the Force. Once during each of your control phases, may: Select one character present to be power or forfeit +1 for remainder of turn. OR Use 2 Force to cancel any seeker present.
lore: Tshhhh. Tshhhh. Zap! "Look ... good against remotes is one thing. Good against the living, that's something else."
name: Remote

gametext: May add 2 'riders' (passengers). Bantha ability = 1/2. May move as a 'react.' Whenever a battle was just initiated at same site, one Tusken Raider present (your choice) is 'trampled' (immediately lost).
lore: Fled into the wilderness after mistreatment by a young Tusken Raider. Raised by moisture farmer. Friendly toward strangers, but attacks Tusken Raiders on sight.
name: Rogue Bantha

gametext: Use 1 Force to deploy on your Y-wing or B-wing. May target a starship using 1 Force. Draw destiny. If destiny > target's defense value, all starship weapons deployed on target are lost, armor or maneuver = 0 and hyperspeed = 0.
lore: ArMek SW-4 turret-mounted ion cannon. Bursts of ionized energy fuse and overload target's mechanical and computer systems. Allows ships to be captured and boarded.
name: SW-4 Ion Cannon

gametext: During your control phase, target one weapon, device or vehicle at same site as your Undercover spy. Draw destiny. If destiny > target's deploy cost, target is lost (may be stolen instead if spy also a thief). OR Cancel Informant.
lore: Poorly equipped Rebels must rely on clandestine strikes against the massive Imperial military. Computer 'slicing' and system tampering have proven most effective.
name: Sabotage

dark_side_text: Your characters may enter/exit here for 1 Force each. "Nighttime conditions" here.
gametext: Deploy on your Sandcrawler. Each Jawa is forfeit +2 here. "Nighttime conditions" here.   Your characters may enter/exit here for 1 Force each. "Nighttime conditions" here.
light_side_text: Deploy on your Sandcrawler. Each Jawa is forfeit +2 here. "Nighttime conditions" here.
name: Sandcrawler: Loading Bay

gametext: At any time, may use 1 Force to remove (lose) a Restraining Bolt at same site. Receives an extra power +1 when 'protected' by Sai'torr Kal Fas.
lore: Hrchek Kal Fas, a male Saurin from Durkteel, is a typical droid trader. Scours the "invisible market" for the best droid prices. Guarded by his cousin Sai'torr.
name: Saurin

gametext: Deploy on your side of table. Radar Scanner is immune to Sense. If Radar Scanner is played against an opponent who has more than 13 cards in hand, opponent loses all Jawas, Tusken Raiders and stormtroopers found there.
lore: Specialized scanner technicians examine scanner output to identify the presence of life forms. Experienced operators can even identify species and gender.
name: Scanner Techs

gametext: Use 1 Force to deploy on your non-creature vehicle. Adds 1 to power and landspeed. Once per turn, when you play Radar Scanner, you may use 1 Force to move one additional Effect or Interrupt card found in opponent's hand to Used Pile.
lore: Monitors all nearby traffic in exterior locations. Takes advantage of multiple backup systems to minimize breakdowns under harsh conditions.
name: Sensor Panel

gametext: Deploy on your warrior to give that warrior \b scout\b0  skill. That warrior may move as a 'react.' OR Deploy on your scout. When that scout 'reacts,' it is power +2 for remainder of turn. (Immune to Alter.)
lore: Veteran officer of the Old Republic who retired from active duty after the Clone Wars. Makes a living in the Outer Rim Territories passing on his scouting expertise.
name: Solomahal

gametext: During your control phase, fire one of your weapons. If Han firing, may add 1 to each weapon destiny draw. (A seeker may be targeted by a character weapon using defense value of 4.) Any 'hit' targets are immediately lost.
lore: "I've been looking forward to this for a long time." "Yes, I'll bet you have." Han abruptly ended his conversation with Greedo and flipped Wuher a credit to pay for the cleanup.
name: Sorry About The Mess

gametext: May be deployed even without presence or Force icons. May add 3 pilots and 4 passengers. Has ship-docking capability. Permanent pilot provides ability of 2.
lore: Royal House of Alderaan consular ship. Used by Princess Leia for Imperial Senate business (and secret Rebel espionage). Captured by the \ul Devastator\ul0  over Tatooine.
name: Tantive IV

gametext: Once per game, use 2 Force to deploy on Dantooine system. Target Death Star. Opponent may not play Commence Primary Ignition until target reaches Dantooine, canceling Utinni Effect.
lore: "You would prefer another target? A military target? Then name the system!"
name: They're On Dantooine

gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. When piloting Gold 2, also adds 1 to maneuver and (when in Death Star: Trench) adds 1 to total of Attack Run.
lore: Piloted Gold 2 as defensive cover for Gold Leader during attack run in Death Star trench at the Battle of Yavin.
name: Tiree

gametext: May 'fly' (move) only during your deploy phase, up to two sites away, for 1 Force. Power +1 at Trash Compactor, any Dagobah site or same site as Dark Waters or Tarkin.
lore: This male Brizzit, from the planet Jandoon, is hiding from the Imperials on the remote world Tatooine. He hopes to procure passage to the Outer Rim before the Empire finds him.
name: Tzizvvt

gametext: Deploy on your spy at a site and cross spy to opponent's side. Spy is now Undercover. During your deploy phase, may voluntarily "break cover" (lose Effect) if at a site. (Immune to Alter.)
lore: Alliance Intelligence expends considerable resources to infiltrate the Imperial military bureaucracy, but the ISB's security sweeps make these shadowy operations dangerous.
name: Undercover

gametext: Adds 3 to power of anything he pilots. When piloting Red 2, also adds 2 to maneuver and draws one battle destiny if not able to otherwise. May use 1 Force to take one Corellian Slip into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle.
lore: Highly decorated Corellian. Piloted Red 2 at the Battle of Yavin. A wealthy orphan, he bought a freighter with his inheritance. First joined the Alliance as weapons \b smuggler\b0.
name: Wedge Antilles

gametext: Use 3 Force to deploy on table and stack one just-played interrupt here. To play any new Interrupt of the same name, player must first stack it here and use +1 Force for each Interrupt in stack, even if Interrupt is normally free. (Immune to Control.)
lore: Moisture farmers like Own Lars must be on the lookout for repeated (and blatant) ploys by Jawas.
name: What're You Tryin' To Push On Us?

gametext: If Chewie is defending a battle alone at a site, add two battle destiny. OR Use 3 Force to take Chewie into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle. OR Scare off (lose) one 'mouse' droid on table.
lore: "GHRRRRAARRRRHG!"
name: Wookiee Roar

gametext: * Replaces 3 Y-wings at one location (Y-wings go to Used Pile). May add 3 pilots or passengers. Permanent pilots provide total ability of 3.
lore: The Rebel Alliance deploys starfighters in triangular formations to minimize exposure to enemy fire. Two function as wingmen to cover one leader.
name: Y-wing Assault Squadron

dark_side_text: Force drain +1 here. If you control, subtract 1 from total of Attack Run.
gametext: If you control, with a leader here, may add 1 to total of Attack Run.   Force drain +1 here. If you control, subtract 1 from total of Attack Run.
light_side_text: If you control, with a leader here, may add 1 to total of Attack Run.
name: Yavin 4: Briefing Room

gametext: If you control, with a leader here, your starships are each power +1 at Death Star system.   Force drain +1 here.
light_side_text: If you control, with a leader here, your starships are each power +1 at Death Star system.
name: Yavin 4: Massassi Ruins

gametext: Cancel I'm On The Leader. (Immune to Sense.) OR Use 1 Force during an Attack Run. Move one TIE in Death Star: Trench (your choice) to Death Star system for free. Add 1 to total of Attack Run if lead starfighter has matching pilot aboard.
lore: "Now let's blow this thing and go home!"
name: You're All Clear Kid!

gametext: Where present, just before opponent draws battle destiny, you may use 1 Force to reduce opponent's total battle destiny by 1.
lore: Snivvian also known as 'Snaggletooth.' A tortured artist who, like most Snivvians, is driven to live out the stories he creates.
name: Zutton

gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. Whenever you deploy a weapon or device from hand at same location, activate 1 Force as a 'kickback.' Limit of one Advosze per location.
lore: Typical of male Advosze, Bom Vimdin despises those of his own species. Pessimistic and territorial, he is a lone \b smuggler\b0  who prefers to work for corrupt officials.
name: Advosze

gametext: Use 3 Force to deploy on opponent's side of table. All opponent's starships with a [Nav Computer] are deploy +1.
lore: Imperial pilots often target astromechs aboard Rebel starfighters in an attempt to prevent hyper-escapes. Scarcity of undamaged astromechs can delay starfighter deployment.
name: Astromech Shortage

gametext: Deploy on a captured starship. Your characters present with captured starship may battle opponent's characters aboard it (as if present together at a site). Effect canceled if starship escapes or is stolen.
lore: Stormtroopers blasted through the main airlock of the \ul Tantive IV\ul0. The Rebel soldiers' attempt to defend the intrusion was no match for the Empire's superior firepower.
name: Besieged

gametext: May add 3 passengers. Permanent pilot provides ability of 1. May move as a 'react.' * Landspeed = 3. OR Up to 3 characters may shuttle to or from same site for free.
lore: This light, \b enclosed\b0  shuttle is used for courier runs to large orbiting transports.
name: Bespin Motors Void Spider THX 1138

gametext: May add 1 pilot. May deploy with a pilot as a 'react' to a battle where you have a TIE (for free if TIE is Black 2 or 3).
lore: TIE fighter flown by DS-61-4 at the Battle of Yavin. Scored a hit on Red 5 during the confrontation.
name: Black 4

gametext: Once during each of your control phases, you may use 2 Force to take one Scanning Crew into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle.
lore: Docking bay security officer. \b Leader\b0. Honored for bravery aboard the Star Destroyer \ul Thunderflare\ul0  where he rescued five officers from the wreckage of a shuttle crash.
name: Captain Khurgee

gametext: Use 1 Force to target a starfighter having one or more permanent pilots. Draw destiny. If destiny > 2, deploy on starfighter to remove all permanent pilots (otherwise, Effect is lost). May add one pilot for each permanent pilot removed. (Immune to Alter.)
lore: Pilots are often reassigned at the last minute for a variety of tactical reasons. Darth Vader ordered DS-61-2 and DS-61-3 to accompany him to the Battle of Yavin.
name: Come With Me

gametext: During your control phase, fire Superlaser as follows: \par \b Name the System:\b0  Use X Force to target a planet system Death Star is orbiting. \par \b You May Fire When Ready:\b0  Draw Destiny. \par \b Stand By:\b0  If (destiny +Y -Z) > 8, target system is "blown away" and this card is lost. Otherwise, this card is used and one Death Star Gunner on table is lost (your choice). \par X = total sites at target. \par Y = total Death Star sites where opponent has no presence. \par Z = opponent's choice of X or total sites at one Rebel Base (Yavin 4 or Hoth).
name: Commence Primary Ignition

gametext: May add 6 pilots, 8 passengers, 2 vehicles and 4 TIEs. Has ship-docking capability. Permanent pilot provides ability of 1. Just after initiating battle against \ul Falcon\ul0, may peek at opponent's hand.
lore: One of the Imperial cruisers that chased the \ul Millennium Falcon\ul0  from Tatooine. It scanned the \ul Falcon\ul0  just before Han punched his starship to lightspeed.
name: Conquest

gametext: Adds 3 to power of anything he pilots. When piloting Black 4, also may draw one battle destiny if not able to otherwise. May use 1 Force to take one Lone Pilot into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle.
lore: Imperial pilot nicknamed "Dark Curse." Survived assaults against several dissenter worlds including Ralltiir and Mon Calamari. Intends to retire after his next combat mission.
name: DS-61-4

gametext: * Power = 1 + total ability of all victims whose soup was eaten. Once per battle, may use 1 Force to "eat the soup" of (place out of play) one opposing non-droid character just lost or forfeited at same site.
lore: Anzati assassin. Cheek-folds hide proboscises which allow him to "eat the soup" (consume the life Force) of his victims. Smokes t'bac. Currently working for Jabba.
name: Dannik Jerriko

characteristics: \b Black Sun agent\b0, \b bounty hunter\b0, \b gunner\b0
gametext: Adds 3 to power of anything he pilots. Adds 1 to weapon destiny draws of anything he is aboard as a passenger.
lore: Cocky \b gunner\b0  and \b bounty hunter\b0. Maintains a residence on Nar Shaddaa, the spaceport moon of the Hutt homeworld. To his companions' delight, he's nearly as good as he boasts.
name: Danz Borin

gametext: Deploy on any exterior planet site (except Hoth) or any interior vehicle site. Opponent's Force drains are -1 here. (Immune to Alter when a swamp creature is present.)
lore: Swamp predators require damp and cluttered environments to enhance their camouflage and stealth. "Something just moved past my leg."
name: Dark Waters

dark_side_text: X = parsec of current position. Deploys only at Parsec 0. Hyperspeed = 1. Immune to Revolution. If this is your starting location, Light Side goes first in game.
gametext: X = parsec of current position. Deploys only at Parsec 0. Hyperspeed = 1. Immune to Revolution. If this is your starting location, Light Side goes first in game.
name: Death Star

gametext: If on Death Star: \b Cumulatively\b0  adds 2 to total of Commence Primary Ignition. OR During your control phase, may send this gunner to your Used Pile and take Superlaser into hand from Reserve Deck; reshuffle.
lore: Most gunners in the Imperial Navy once aspired to be TIE pilots, but lacked sufficient skills to fly starfighters. A few were assigned to the Death Star to man the main artillery.
name: Death Star Gunner

gametext: Use 2 Force to deploy on Docking Bay 327. At the end of a battle at Death Star system, may target an opponent's starship present (except a Mon Calamari Star Cruiser) using 2 Force. Draw two destiny. Target captured if total destiny > defense value.
lore: "Why are we still moving towards it?"
name: Death Star Tractor Beam

dark_side_text: If you control, with a leader here, may add 1 to total of Commence Primary Ignition.
gametext: Force drain +1 here. If you control, may subtract 1 from total of Commence Primary Ignition.   If you control, with a leader here, may add 1 to total of Commence Primary Ignition.
light_side_text: Force drain +1 here. If you control, may subtract 1 from total of Commence Primary Ignition.
name: Death Star: Conference Room

gametext: Under "nighttime conditions," may use 1 Force to 'hide' (exclude himself) from a battle. While at a site affected by Revolution, opponent must lose 1 Force during your control phase.
lore: Male Defel from Af'El. This species, also known as 'wraiths', is capable of warping light around themselves, becoming difficult to see at dusk.
name: Defel

gametext: * Ferocity = (power/ferocity of last character or creature eaten) + destiny. Habitat: exterior Dagobah sites, Trash Compactor and Dark Waters.
lore: "Garbage squid" from Vodran's jungles. Changes color to match last meal. When unfed, turns transparent. Eats almost anything. Flexible eyestalk. 7 tentacles. Up to 6 meters long.
name: Dianoga

gametext: Use 1 Force to deploy on your TIE. May target a starship using 1 Force. Draw destiny. Subtract 2 if targeting a capital starship. Target hit if destiny > defense value.
lore: Sienar Fleet Systems' latest laser cannon prototype increases the firepower of most Imperial TIEs - but many Moffs consider the weapon too expensive for widespread use.
name: Enhanced TIE Laser Cannon

gametext: USED: Cancel all Revolutions in play (owner loses 1 Force for each). LOST: If Vader or Vader's Custom TIE was just lost, relocate that card to Used Pile. OR Relocate to Used Pile one Imperial just lost from any Death Star location.
lore: A panic move by Black 2 sent Vader spinning wildly from the Death Star trench - ironically sparing his life. His destiny would be fulfilled another time.
name: Evader

gametext: During the damage segment of a battle you lost, if you have no cards left that can be forfeited, cancel all remaining battle damage. (Immune to Sense.) OR Cancel Nightfall.
lore: \b Dejarik\b0  of creature from Clak'dor VII. Ghhhk rise with the dawn, screeching their mating calls across the jungle. Locals use their skin oils as a healing salve.
name: Ghhhk

characteristics: \b Black Sun agent\b0, \b bounty hunter\b0, \b Rodian\b0
gametext: During opponent's control phase, may 'threaten' one smuggler at same site. Opponent may use all Force Pile cards to cancel threat, allowing you to activate same amount. Otherwise, draw destiny. If destiny + Greedo's ability > 6, smuggler lost.
lore: Male Rodian \b bounty hunter\b0. Sent by Jabba to capture Han. Arrogant, overconfident and not too bright. Trained by bounty hunters Nataz and Goa, who betrayed him to Thuku.
name: Greedo

gametext: Once during each of your deploy phases, you may place, face down, one card from your hand or Force Pile under Hem, as "salt consumption." If Hem lost, cards underneath also lost. * Power = 1 + number of cards underneath.
lore: Male \b scout\b0  from Cona. As with many Arconas, Hem has succumbed to the power of salt, an addiction indicated by his gold eye color.
name: Hem Dazon

gametext: Deploy on your side of table. Scanning Crew is immune to Sense. If Scanning Crew is played against an opponent who has 13 or more cards in hand, opponent also loses all cards with 'Rebel' in the title found there.
lore: Full Imperial scans include full-spectrum transceivers, dedicated energy receptors, crystal gravfield traps, and hyperwave signal interceptors.
name: Hyperwave Scan

gametext: Deploy on your IT-O. Once during each of your control phases, if present with a captive (or with an imprisoned captive): You may ask one yes-or-no question about cards in opponent's hand. Opponent must answer truthfully or lose 1 Force. OR May add 1 to Force drain where present.
lore: Truth drugs like Bavo Six decrease resistance to interrogation. The enormous needle adds psychological pressure, facilitating the interrogation process.
name: Hypo

gametext: Target opponent's starfighter making an Attack Run. Draw destiny. Add 1 for each of your TIEs in Death Star: Trench. If total destiny > maneuver, starfighter is lost. OR Add 1 to weapon destiny draws of any starfighter for remainder of this turn.
lore: In the defense of the Death Star at the Battle of Yavin, Darth Vader took the lead attacker, supported by his wingmen Black 2 and Black 3.
name: I'm On The Leader

gametext: When at Detention Block Corridor, adds X to your Force drains there, where X = number of captives here. Immune to Restraining Bolt.
lore: Floating prisoner interrogation droid. Uses probes and needles to dispense truth drugs and perform 'surgery.' Sensors determine subject's pain threshold and truthfulness.
name: IT-O (Eyetee-Oh)

gametext: Adds 1 to forfeit of each of your other Imperials (except leaders) at same site.
lore: Typical Imperial \b leader\b0. Uses constant training and crisis simulations to help maintain high performance levels. Commander Daine Jir is known to be bold and outspoken.
name: Imperial Commander

gametext: "Dejarik Rules" in effect here. Site converted by Dejarik Hologameboard.   "Dejarik Rules" in effect here.
light_side_text: "Dejarik Rules" in effect here. Site converted by Dejarik Hologameboard.
name: Imperial Holotable

gametext: If opponent is generating at least 4 more Force than you, deploy on a location to cancel all Force generation at that location. OR Deploy on a location. It is now immune to Revolution.
lore: "There's nothing you could have done Luke, had you been there. You'd have been killed too."
name: Imperial Justice

gametext: Adds 1 to forfeit of your other troopers at same site. When moving with a 'squad' of exactly three other troopers, all four move for 1 Force. Imperial Trooper Guards at same site may move.
lore: Captain Mod Terrik, a typical officer of the Desert Sands sandtrooper unit. Fearless and highly motivated. Willing to sacrifice as many troops as necessary.
name: Imperial Squad Leader

gametext: If a battle was just initiated at same site as your Undercover spy, your characters at adjacent sites may move there as a 'react' (for free). OR Cancel Sabotage.
lore: The Empire's network of spies and petty informants allows Imperial operatives to discover and react to Rebel assaults before they occur.
name: Informant

gametext: Deploy on your Jawa. May target a character or creature for free. Draw destiny. If destiny -1 > defense value, target hit. If destiny = 0, Jawa Blaster 'explodes' (weapon and character firing it are lost).
lore: Built from scavenged parts, Jawa blaster are not required to adhere to any design standards. An etching on this stock warns "datinni greb zroom."
name: Jawa Blaster

dark_side_text: Force drain +1 here. If you control, all Wookiees on table are forfeit -3.
gametext: Your starships with any Wookiee aboard are power and forfeit +2 here.   Force drain +1 here. If you control, all Wookiees on table are forfeit -3.
light_side_text: Your starships with any Wookiee aboard are power and forfeit +2 here.
name: Kashyyyk

dark_side_text: If you occupy with exactly 2 starships, your total power here is +2 and Tonnika Sisters anywhere are doubled.
gametext: If you occupy with exactly 2 starships, your total power here is +2.   If you occupy with exactly 2 starships, your total power here is +2 and Tonnika Sisters anywhere are doubled.
light_side_text: If you occupy with exactly 2 starships, your total power here is +2.
name: Kiffex

gametext: Use 1 Force to deploy on table. Each opponent's destiny draw, you do the following: (0) Put top used card in hand; (1) lose 1 Force; (2) activate 1 Force; (3) lose this Effect; (4) retrieve 1 Force; (5) deploy a character for free; (6+) nothing.
lore: Tusken Raiders, Jawas and other desert dwellers believe that krayt dragon bones possess mystical powers that can bring good or bad luck.
name: Krayt Dragon Bones

gametext: Deploy between any two interior mobile sites. To pass, a character must have (power + ability) > 4 or use a Lift Tube (all other vehicles are blocked). Laser Gate defense value = 3; may be targeted by a character weapon from either site.
lore: Security corridors are guarded by a grid of laser emplacements which can be activated upon demand to seal off sensitive areas from intrusion.
name: Laser Gate

gametext: Deploys for 1 Force to an unoccupied site. Deploys and moves like an undercover spy. When present with Leia (or warrior) of ability < 3, choose one to be immediately lost (treat as an "all cards" situation). Seeker is also lost.
lore: Military version of a 'remote.' Programmed to stalk specific targets or secondary targets. Heat and light sensors track with fatal accuracy. Can stow away on starships.
name: Leia Seeker

gametext: For each other musician present, adds a "cover charge" of 1 to the Force required to move or deploy each character to same site.
lore: Bith mercenary. Male back-up to Kloo Horn player in Figrin D'an's band. Only \b musician\b0, besides Doikk, who has not lost ownership of his instrument to Figrin.
name: Lirin Car'n

gametext: While at Docking Control Room 327, adds 2 to your total power at Docking Bay 327. Once during each of your control phases, if at same site as an Undercover spy, may draw destiny. Spy's "cover is broken" if destiny = spy's ability.
lore: Gantry officer charged with maintaining magnetic field, atmosphere and security in Death Star docking bay. After mission on Ralltiir, paranoid about infiltration by Rebel spies.
name: Lt. Pol Treidum

gametext: Power +2 when at Detention Block Corridor or Detention Block Control Room. Also, power +2 when an opponent's alien is present (+3 if alien is a Wookiee, Talz or Ewok).
lore: Demoted after a superior blamed him for a clerical error. Considered a bully by fellow officers. Fanatically supports the New Order doctrine of alien subjugation.
name: Lt. Shann Childsen

gametext: Deploy on your sandcrawler. Once during each of your control phases, may target one character present. Draw destiny. If destiny > character's ability, "suck up" character (relocate to related interior sandcrawler site or owner's Used Pile).
lore: 'Slurp.'
name: Magnetic Suction Tube

gametext: Deploy on Death Star: Trench. Opponent must make maneuver checks for starfighters leaving the trench. For each starfighter, owner draws destiny. If destiny + maneuver < 5, starfighter is lost.
lore: "Luke, at that speed will you be able to pull out in time?"
name: Maneuver Check

gametext: May add 1 driver and 1 passenger. Moves free if Jabba or any bounty hunter aboard. May move for free as a 'react' to a battle where your thief, smuggler or bounty hunter is participating.
lore: \b Enclosed\b0  landspeeder often used by nefarious characters due to its luxury and evasive capabilities. Features include automated steering and fine Corellian leather.
name: Mobquet A-1 Deluxe Floater

gametext: USED: If opponent has 13 or more cards in hand, place all but 8 (random selection) in Used Pile. LOST: Use 4 Force to reveal opponent's hand. All cards opponent has two or more of in hand are lost.
lore: \b Dejarik\b0  creature. Savage predator from remote deserts of Soccorro. Respected and honored by Soccorran hunters; considered "good luck" by superstitious smugglers.
name: Monnok

gametext: When opponent is losing Force from Force drains at the same or an adjacent site, lost Force must come from Reserve Deck if possible.
lore: Jabba's Nimbanel accountant. Inside contacts allow him to disrupt the cash flow of the Hutt's enemies. He knows a mistake could make him the next write-off.
name: Mosep

gametext: If opponent just deployed four or more characters to same location this turn, prevent all of those characters from battling this turn. OR If opponent just 'reacted' to a battle, cancel the battle.
lore: \b Dejarik\b0  of a Ng'ok war beast. Foul temper gives rise to bad feelings. Has razor-sharp retractable claws. Used in many systems to frighten off potential attackers.
name: Ng'ok

gametext: Adds 2 to power of anything he pilots. When at a Death Star site, Imperial starships may move to the Death Star system as a 'react.'
lore: This Imperial Intelligence \b leader\b0  has a proven track record for predicting Rebel fleet movements. His coordination of starship maneuvers has saved many vulnerable bases.
name: Officer Evax

gametext: If Nabrun Leids just completed a transport, use 2 Force. Nabrun is lost and all Rebels transported are captured. (Immune to Sense.) OR Prevent a just-deployed smuggler from moving this turn. OR Cancel a Kessel Run.
lore: Greedo cheskopokuta klees ruya Solo. Hoko yanee boopa gush Cantina. Cheeco wa Solo's anye nyuma Greedo vakee. Jabba kul steeka et en anpaw.
name: Oo-ta Goo-ta, Solo?

gametext: Use 2 Force to deploy on an opponent's droid (except R2-D2 and C-3PO), 1 on your droid. When either player draws a destiny matching the number of characters at same site, droid 'explodes' (all characters present with Effect are lost).
lore: Imperial slicers imbed a secret command in a droid's primary performance banks. A predetermined trigger causes a power overload, destroying the droid and anything nearby.
name: Program Trap

gametext: While aboard any starfighter, adds 1 to power, maneuver and hyperspeed. When at a Scomp link during your draw phase, may use 1 Force to peek at top three cards of your Reserve Deck.
lore: R2 units are known for expertise in computer uplinking. R2-Q2 spent several decades serving with an Imperial reconnaissance fleet in the Expansion Region.
name: R2-Q2 (Artoo-Kyootoo)

gametext: While aboard a capital starship, adds 1 to power and 2 to hyperspeed, and that starship is immune to attrition < 4. While at Death Star: Central Core, hyperspeed of Death Star system = 2.
lore: R3 units have larger memory and more advanced circuitry than their R1 predecessors, allowing for more efficient astrogation plots. R3-T6 served on the Death Star.
name: R3-T6 (Arthree-Teesix)

gametext: While aboard any starship, adds 1 to power and maneuver. During your control phase, if aboard your starship damaged by an ion cannon, restores armor/maneuver and hyperspeed.
lore: Seldom used for navigation purposes, R5 units are known for their ability to perform hull maintenance and repair damage caused by ionization.
name: R5-A2 (Arfive-Aytoo)

dark_side_text: \ul Devastator\ul0  is power +1 here and may move to or from here for free.
gametext: \ul Tantive IV\ul0  is power +1 here   \ul Devastator\ul0  is power +1 here and may move to or from here for free.
name: Ralltiir

gametext: Once during each of your control phases, may lose 1 Force to take one vehicle, droid, weapon or device from opponent's Lost Pile or Crash Site Memorial into hand to use as your own.
lore: Ranat \b thief\b0 and scavenger from Aralia. Regularly trades with Jawas. Adept at pilfering items without alerting the owner. Willing to steal anything, even trash.
name: Reegesk

gametext: Adds 1 to power of anything he pilots. When piloting Black 2, Black 3 or Black 4, also adds 1 to maneuver and draws one battle destiny if not able to otherwise.
lore: Injuries kept Lord Vader's best TIE wingman out of the primary wave of starfighters. He remains on reserve duty, ready to replace lost pilots.
name: Reserve Pilot

gametext: During your deploy phase, use X Force to rearrange all interior Death Star sites, where X = total number of those sites. All cards at a given site move along with that site. OR Cancel On The Edge.
lore: Strategically retracted bridges can frustrate enemy movement, forcing routing plans to be rearranged.
name: Retract The Bridge

gametext: Adds 1 to power of anything he pilots. Adds 1 to power of each of your bounty hunters and smugglers (but subtracts 1 from Greedo's power) at same site.
lore: Thuku is a typical male Rodian. Sent to hunt down Greedo by Navik the Red, head of the Chattza tribe. Rodians enjoy "the hunt," so many are employed as assassins.
name: Rodian

dark_side_text: Deploy on your Sandcrawler. Each Jawa is forfeit +2 here. "Nighttime conditions" here.
gametext: Your characters may enter/exit here for 1 Force each. "Nighttime conditions" here.   Deploy on your Sandcrawler. Each Jawa is forfeit +2 here. "Nighttime conditions" here.
light_side_text: Your characters may enter/exit here for 1 Force each. "Nighttime conditions" here.
name: Sandcrawler: Droid Junkheap

gametext: During your control phase, fire one of your weapons. If URoRRuR'R'R firing, may add 2 to each weapon destiny draw. (A seeker may be targeted by a character weapon using defense value of 4.) Any 'hit' targets are immediately lost.
lore: Tusken Raiders often attack lone desert travelers at long range. Their cowardly nature leads them to rely on surprise attacks rather than direct engagement.
name: Sniper

gametext: Deploy on Kessel (may not be moved). Target one captive and one trooper to escort captive. When targets reach Utinni Effect, retrieve Force equal to captive's forfeit (captive and Utinni Effect lost). If trooper lost en route, captive released.
lore: Captives sent to the Kessel spice mines spend the rest of their lives digging for glitterstim, a spice sold throughout the galaxy by smugglers and crime lords.
name: Spice Mines Of Kessel

gametext: If a battle was just initiated at an interior site, use 1 Force; for remainder of battle, all characters of ability > 2 and all leaders (on both sides) are simultaneously excluded from that battle.
lore: Stormtroopers are trained to stun, not kill, priority targets in order to split enemy forces and hold the leaders for interrogation. Stun effects wear off, requiring efficient action.
name: Stunning Leader

gametext: Deploy on Death Star system at parsec 0. May target a capital starship at Death Star system, or at a system it orbits, using 4 Force. Draw two destiny. Target hit if total destiny > defense value.
lore: The Death Star has more firepower than the combined might of the entire Imperial fleet. Enormous generators power the devastating planet-destroying weapon.
name: Superlaser

gametext: Deploy on your non-thief to give that character \b thief\b0  skill. Once during each of your control phases, may target one device at same site. Draw destiny. If destiny < target's destiny number, it is stolen. OR Deploy on a weapon to prevent theft. (Immune to Alter.)
lore: Petty criminals throughout the galaxy often earn extra money by teaching their trade to initiates. Thievery has become more popular as the Empire tightens its grip.
name: Swilla Corey

gametext: * Replaces 3 TIE/lns at one location (TIE/lns go to Used Pile). Permanent pilots provide total ability of 3.
lore: Imperial strategy relies on quantity over quality. Although many of their pilots have low motivation, this is compensated by 'wolfpack' group tactics.
name: TIE Assault Squadron

gametext: Permanent pilot provides ability of 1. You may deploy cards to same system or sector as a 'react'.
lore: Reconnaissance starfighter. Often deployed first to gather detailed information on enemy starship movement before full fleet engagement.
name: TIE Vanguard

gametext: "Bluff Rules" in effect here.   "Bluff Rules" in effect here.
name: Tatooine: Bluffs

gametext: After using Ommni Box, peek at top X cards of pile or deck just shuffled, where X = number of other musicians at same site. May re-shuffle without peeking.
lore: Male Bith \b musician\b0. Plays Ommni Box in Figrin D'an's band. Lost ownership of instrument to Figrin while gambling.
name: Tech Mo'r

gametext: If opponent just played an Interrupt, use 1 Force to deploy on table. That Interrupt is played out but is then 'grabbed' (played here but is out of play). Any new Interrupts of the same name are unique (*). (Immune to Control.)
lore: Dianogas use their seven tentacles for both locomotion and catching food. The few survivors of such attacks claim that a dianoga tentacle has the strength of a hydro-clamp.
name: Tentacle

gametext: Use 3 Force to deploy on table and stack one just-played Interrupt here. To play any new Interrupt of the same name, player must first stack it here and use +1 Force for each Interrupt in stack, even if Interrupt is normally free. (Immune to Control).
lore: Luke's dream of joining the Academy often distracted him from his chores, sometimes resulting in his having to pay the price for his impatience.
name: There'll Be Hell To Pay

gametext: Cancel I'm Here To Rescue You, Plastoid Armor, Out Of Commission, Alternatives To Fighting, Cell 2187 or Ewok Rescue.
lore: "When you came in here, didn't you have a plan for getting out?"
name: This Is Some Rescue!

gametext: Use 2 Force to deploy on your Star Destroyer. At the end of a battle at same system or sector, may target an opponent's starship present (except Mon Calamari Star Cruiser) using 2 Force. Draw destiny. Target captured if destiny > defense value.
lore: Captures enemy vessels for boarding. When used in conjunction with an ion cannon, tractor beams can ensnare even the most maneuverable starships.
name: Tractor Beam

gametext: While he is on Tatooine, Local Trouble and Look Sir, Droids are Used Interrupts. Opponent may select target when using Friendly Fire at same site as Felth.
lore: Dispatched to Tatooine to apprehend renegade droids fleeing the \ul Tantive IV\ul0. Suspected to have misgivings about Imperial methods. Allegedly shot his commander in the back.
name: Trooper Davin Felth

gametext: Deploy on opponent's side as an Undercover spy (except that if present during a battle at a site, adds its power to Light Side). If spy's "cover is broken," the above "game text" is canceled and Light Side may use as if stolen.
lore: This protocol droid served in the House of Alderaan's Diplomatic Corps. Imperials altered its programming for espionage, making the droid an unwitting \b spy\b0  for the Empire.
name: U-3PO (Yoo-Threepio)

gametext: Deploys only on Tatooine. When at same site as another Tusken Raider, may draw one battle destiny if not able to otherwise.
lore: \b Leader\b0  of a Tusken Raider tribe. Unafraid of machines. Skilled hunter and marksman. Raids moisture farms for water. Roams the Jundland Wastes in search of unwary travelers.
name: URoRRuR'R'R

gametext: Use 1 Force to deploy on URoRRuR'R'R or Chief Bast, 3 on your non-droid character. May target a character or creature using 1 Force. Draw destiny. Subtract 1 if targeting a character. Add 2 if targeting a creature. Target hit if total destiny > defense value.
lore: Owning a hunting rifle is an important status symbol in Tusken culture. URoRRuR'R'R scavenged this weapon from a starship wreck near Anchorhead.
name: URoRRuR'R'R's Hunting Rifle

gametext: Deploy on your spy at a site and cross spy to opponent's side. Spy is now Undercover. During your deploy phase, may voluntarily "break cover" (lose Effect) if at a site. (Immune to Alter.)
lore: The Empire maintains a network of spies attempting to infiltrate the Rebel Alliance or disinform their operatives.
name: Undercover

gametext: May add 4 pilots, 6 passengers, 1 vehicle and 3 TIEs. Has ship-docking capability. Permanent pilot provides ability of 1. Adds 1 to your total power in battles at related planet sites.
lore: Commissioned by the Old Republic at end of the Clone Wars, Rendili StarDrive's \ul Victory\ul0-class starship is atmosphere-capable but has a low sublight speed.
name: Victory-Class Star Destroyer

gametext: * Forfeit value begins at 7. When 'forfeited,' droid remains in play (unless 'hit'), but forfeit value is reduced by the amount of attrition or battle damage absorbed. Droid lost when forfeit value reaches zero.
lore: Multi-armed maintenance droid fiercely loyal to the Empire. Specializes in extending effective operational life of Imperial resources. Nicknamed for an insect from Eriadu.
name: WED15-l7 'Septoid' Droid

gametext: Use 1 Force if opponent's character is about to be lost or forfeited from battle. It is captured instead (character is first restored to normal). OR Use X Force to capture all characters on board a captured starship, where X = twice the number of characters.
lore: "You are part of the Rebel Alliance, and a traitor. Take her away!"
name: We Have A Prisoner
